  "prompt": "How did Kakashi get the Sharingan?",
  "response": "Kakashi Hatake obtained his Sharingan through a tragic and significant event involving his teammate, Obito Uchiha. During a mission in the Third Great Ninja War, Kakashi, Obito, and Rin were ambushed by enemy ninja. Obito was crushed by a boulder while trying to save Kakashi and believed he was about to die. Before Obito succumbed to his injuries, he entrusted Kakashi with his Sharingan as a gift and a symbol of their friendship.\n\nThe medical ninja of the team, Rin, performed the eye transplant surgery on Kakashi on Obito\u2019s request. Kakashi\u2019s left eye, which was originally his own, was replaced with Obito's left Sharingan eye. This gave Kakashi the ability to use the Sharingan, despite not being an Uchiha himself. However, because Kakashi lacked the Uchiha lineage, he could not deactivate the Sharingan, causing it to remain active and drain his chakra constantly.\n\nLater, it was revealed that Obito survived the incident, but he was presumed dead by Kakashi and the others. This event had a profound impact on Kakashi\u2019s life and became a defining moment in his character\u2019s development.",
